casebody.data:
RISER v. WARDEN, CALIFORNIA STATE PRISON. No. 331,

Misc.

Decided February 24, 1959. George T. Davis for appellant. Stanley Mosk, Attorney General of California, Clarence A. Linn, Chief Assistant Attorney General, and Arlo E. Smith, Deputy Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
